Temasek Holdings, Baillie Gifford and Softbank Group Corp Reportedly In Talks To Acquire Stake In Skyscanner form Socttish Equity Partners

Oct 7 15
Telegraph reported that Temasek Holdings (Private) Limited; a Singapore-based investment firm, could be a potential bidder to acquire a 10% stake in Skyscanner Limited, an operator of travel search site, from Sottish Equity Partners LLP, a private equity firm. Skyscanner and Scottish Equity are based in the UK. Reportedly, Baillie Gifford & Co Ltd and SoftBank Group Corp. (TSE:9984) are also in the race to acquire a stake in Skyscanner. Goldman Sachs & Co. is considered to be acting as financial advisor to Skyscanner.



